  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2018-11-28",
    "date": "2019-08-07T19:48:09Z",
    "text": "Guardianship Accountability Act of 2018\n\nThis bill provides resources to support individuals\u00a0who are at least\u00a018 years old and\u00a0who are placed under guardianships because they are\u00a0unable to make safe and sound decisions. Specifically, the bill requires\u00a0the\u00a0Elder Justice Coordinating Council to establish a National Online Resource Center on Guardianship. In addition, the bill expands a\u00a0demonstration grant program\u00a0for\u00a0elder abuse prevention\u00a0to include grants for collecting information about guardianships, training court visitors, and sharing guardian background checks."
  },
